args:
Joachim's men are surrounded, and their only hope
is to finish things before night falls. With renewed
resolve, he takes command and sets forth from the
base for a final showdown with their assailants.
I'll go disrupt their ranks, but I need you\nguys to open a path for me!
Gwaaaugh! It's those weird attacks again!\nFall back! There's no telling what that\nthing will do to you if it hits!
Thanks for clearing the way, fellas.\nVanguard unit, chaaarge!
I've got you covered. Give 'em hell, Aggie!
What are you fools doing?! Hold the line!
But boss, they're pelting us with something\nwe've never seen before!

Why do you think the client's given us
all this armor? We can take some
punishment. Now stop your whinging
and HOLD THEM BACK ALREADY!
Joachim, the enemy is... They're reeling!\nTheir ranks are starting to...to crumble!
Sounds like the diversion's working...\nPhase two, people! Like we planned!
Hit 'em with everything and let's settle it!\nMain force, advance!
Commander Balboa's quarters, a few hours later...
Commander, we've received word\nfrom the field.
Finally. Let's see how things are doing.
Something the matter, Commander?\nYou look a bit green in the gills.\nNot bad news, I hope?
Now I see why you kept so calm.
It seems I lose this round—though I\nmust salute the bravery of your men.
You're taking this rather well. I was\nexpecting a lot of ＂You may have won\nthis round, but... blah blah blah.＂
I didn't realize you had a sense of humor.\nThis is quite the rare sight indeed.
But if that was a request, I'm happy to\noblige. I assumed you knew without my\nsaying it, but this ISN'T over.
No. Weathering one crisis doesn't mean\nthe situation is resolved.
Then let me give you one final chance,\nCommander Kirsty.
Hand over the letter from Litvinov, and I\nwill personally guarantee the safety of\nyour men, as well as your rank.
I see little reason to hesitate. This is your\nmost basic duty as a soldier in the king's\narmy, is it not?
And then what? Am I to sit idly by and\nwatch as my country is swallowed up in\na fetid swamp of corruption?
We are striving day and night to prevent\nprecisely such a fate. I wish you would\nunderstand that.
I would beg to differ. And as ever, I will\nfight to protect my country as my\nconvictions demand.
Commander Kirsty's office, days after the attack...
You asked to see me, Commander?
I wanted to confirm the details of your\nfinal report on the incident the other day.\nHad a few questions for you.
Was there a problem with the brief?
No, it was quite thorough. But there were\na few things beyond its scope I wanted to\nhear straight from the horse's mouth.
What did you gain in course of this\noperation, Joachim?
You brought me here to ask THAT?
Yes, and you're really going to answer.\nEveryone around the base was singing\nyour praises, you know.
Well, I DID learn something from it.\nI'd say I gained exactly what you think\nI did.
A little cold and calculating to give me that\nmanacaster in the hopes it would change\nme and get rid of my doubts, no?
I won't deny it; I have no place for one who\ncan't muster at least that much resolve at\nmy side in the days to come.
So you're gonna accept it, then? His offer?
At the very least, I have sufficient cause to\nsend you. Even if I did nothing, the present\nking's faction will act before long.
Oh, and one more thing: Have you reached\nan answer regarding that promotion?
...Hey, sis. Sorry it's been a while.\nThings are a bit nuts back at work.
Although if I'm honest, I've been putting\noff my visit until I had something to report\nthat'd make you proud...
...But I've got something that fits the bill.\nA promotion.
Ever since I got you killed, I've been afraid\nto accept their offer, but now I finally\nthink I'm ready to take it on.
I learned that the woman who believed in\nme was just as scared as I was, but she\nstill had the guts to make a stand.
So I want to do what I can\nto be there for her.
Don't think this means I forgot about you,\nthough—I'll never forgive myself for what\nhappened to you, as long as I live.
But that's all the more reason I don't want \nto lose anyone else. I can't keep running.
I hope you're watching over me from\nthe great flow of mana, and laughing at\nevery bonehead mistake I make.
It's, um, time to move out. Are you ready?
I'm good. Thanks for coming to get me.
Oh, good! So, next deployment is, um...\nWe're going to see ＂him,＂ right?
That's right. Lead the way, Noelle.\nAnd we have a letter to bring with us,\nI think?
Yes, Chelle entrusted it with me... I just...\nI just hope these talks work out.
Me, too. But hey, that's up to how well we\nnegotiate, right? So let's give it our best.
It's up to us to carve out the future Kirsty's\nhoping for with our own two hands.
